The paper deals with the problem of background modeling in video sequences, which is a common task in computer vision and machine learning. The use of a variational autoencoder framework and deep neural networks suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. The probabilistic nature of the model and the use of unsupervised learning also suggest that it could belong to the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category. The evaluation of the method on surveillance videos suggests that it could also belong to the multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category. Finally, the use of deep neural networks for compressed representation learning suggests that it could belong to the neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE) sub-category.
